article.headline: Southern Illinois 72, Drake 62
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. (AP) -- Tony Young led Southern Illinois with 16 points in a 72-62 win Monday night over Drake. The visiting Bulldogs (10-8, 1-6 Missouri Valley) stayed close in the first half, keeping the Salukis to a 29-25 lead at halftime. But Southern Illinois dominated the entire game in the paint, scoring 24 total points to Drake's 10, and racking up 27 points off Bulldog turnovers. A dunk by Matt Shaw with 12:10 left in the game put Southern Illinois (14-4, 5-2) up 46-35, and the Salukis never looked back. Young went 6-for-6 from the free throw line, hit two 3-pointers and shot 4-for-11 from the field. Randal Falker added 14 points and four rebounds for the Salukis and Shaw contributed 10 points, four rebounds and two steals. Josh Young was the high-scorer for Drake with 13 points, including three 3-pointers.
